00:56:43,680 --> 00:57:00,281
So, just to show you that Yvonne also thinks in terms of crucifixion, he says he's going to go, I'm getting way ahead of where some of you are, but it's not going to affect the who done it part of the story.

683
00:57:00,921 --> 00:57:12,520
But Yvonne is going to go to the trial of Dimitri, and he's going to confess his responsibility for the death of old Karamat.

684
00:57:12,520 --> 00:57:16,921
So, he says, tomorrow, the cross, not the gallows.

685
00:57:16,921 --> 00:57:23,880
Well, we don't know what I can't explain what that means, but that he sees what he's going to do at the trial as the crucifixion.

686
00:57:23,881 --> 00:57:26,200
So, he's got his own version of the cross.

687
00:57:26,200 --> 00:57:27,881
That's the important thing.

688
00:57:28,441 --> 00:57:55,241
And Yvonne is going to suffer, he thinks, by confessing at the trial that his own selfish impulses, his specific evil desires, namely that old Karamat subject, get killed.

689
00:57:59,160 --> 00:58:02,120
But Yvonne can't really take it.

690
00:58:02,921 --> 00:58:09,161
He wants to face his dark side, confess his involvement, so forth, suffer for it.

691
00:58:09,480 --> 00:58:18,041
But instead, out of pride, he decides, he tries to punish himself and thereby show that he's better than everybody else.

692
00:58:18,600 --> 00:58:31,000
Instead of seeing that he's as bad as everybody else, he has this funny move that if he sees and shows that he's as bad as everybody else, that makes him better than everybody else.

693
00:58:31,000 --> 00:58:33,400
Because they aren't just seeing it and showing it.

694
00:58:33,401 --> 00:58:39,520
So he's turning his confession into a kind of, I'm better than you are.

695
00:58:37,560 --> 00:58:41,281
You can see this on 188.

696
00:58:44,160 --> 00:58:53,681
First, you see it in his telling Katerina something which applies to him because he can understand it because it's him too.

697
00:58:53,680 --> 00:59:00,880
He says at the top of 188, your life, Katerina, will be spent in painful brooding over your own feelings, your own heroism, and your own suffering.

698
00:59:01,200 --> 00:59:03,120
