701
00:59:14,401 --> 00:59:15,280
See, this is proud.

702
00:59:15,281 --> 00:59:19,681
Yes, proud it certainly is, and desperate in any case, but a triumph for you.

703
00:59:19,680 --> 00:59:26,641
And the consciousness of it will at last be a source of complete satisfaction and will make you resigned to everything else.

704
00:59:27,361 --> 00:59:34,561
It turns into a weird kind of joy to have managed to pull off this prideful thing.

705
00:59:34,560 --> 00:59:39,840
And this is all part of this masochistic parody of true crucifixion.

706
00:59:43,680 --> 00:59:49,921
He's telling Katerina that her prideful pain is going to be good for her.

707
00:59:51,040 --> 01:00:00,641
And I don't think I need to read this.

708
01:00:02,881 --> 01:00:05,441
No, no, I think not, just a second.

709
01:00:10,560 --> 01:00:16,081
Well, just so you can see the connection, 249, I put it in here for something.

710
01:00:16,080 --> 01:00:24,280
I mean, the Grand Inquisitor, remember I said, thinks of carrying the cross as this kind of masochistic suffering.

711
01:00:24,281 --> 01:00:26,840
So he says about 15 lines from the bottom.

712
01:00:27,160 --> 01:00:28,760
They had borne their cross.

713
01:00:28,761 --> 01:00:33,640
