Now, that's sort of a chance he had to do something good.

850
01:09:56,000 --> 01:10:08,320
And it's just one more thing that when it reminds him of his guilt, he gets in, he feels, he resists doing anything about it.

851
01:10:08,320 --> 01:10:14,160
But let me just try a tiny bit more, because I will finish a kind of unit here.

852
01:10:14,481 --> 01:10:18,961
So he's left him lying on the ground on 587.

853
01:10:19,601 --> 01:10:27,120
And suddenly he feels on 598 a desire to confess.

854
01:10:29,521 --> 01:10:39,360
And all of a sudden, for, we'll see how long, Yvonne is in the saved, it looks like he's in a savable dimension.

855
01:10:39,360 --> 01:10:42,000
The snowstorm, the middle of 598.

856
01:10:42,000 --> 01:10:43,520
The snowstorm was still raging.

857
01:10:43,521 --> 01:10:47,040
He walked the first few steps boldly, but suddenly he began staggering.

858
01:10:47,040 --> 01:10:49,120
It's something physical, he thought, with a grin.

859
01:10:49,120 --> 01:10:51,440
Something like joy was springing up in his heart.

860
01:10:51,440 --> 01:10:53,721
He was conscious of unbounded resolution.

861
01:10:52,881 --> 01:10:57,160
He would make an end to this wavering that had so tortured him of late.

862
01:10:57,400 --> 01:11:02,120
His determination was taken, and now it will not be changed, he thought with relief.

863
01:11:02,120 --> 01:11:04,841
At that moment, he stumbled against something and almost fell down.

864
01:11:04,841 --> 01:11:10,440
Stopping short, he saw at his feet the peasant who he had knocked down, still lying unconscious and motionless.

865
01:11:10,440 --> 01:11:12,921
The snow had almost covered his face.

866
01:11:12,921 --> 01:11:14,841
Yvonne lifted him in his arms.

867
01:11:14,841 --> 01:11:15,961
Can you believe it?

868
01:11:15,961 --> 01:11:20,120
He's never touched another human being in the course of the book, as far as I know.

869
01:11:20,120 --> 01:11:27,160
And now he's got his arms around, and he's practically hugging and carrying the unconscious peasant.

870
01:11:27,481 --> 01:11:37,160
And it looks like, and he's going to go confess, really confess, not out of pride, but out of trying to suffer for what he did that was wrong, in the right way.

871
01:11:37,160 --> 01:11:40,120
But, this is the last comment, it doesn't last.

872
01:11:40,120 --> 01:11:47,961
Just as he reached his own house, he stopped short, asking himself suddenly if he'd better not go at once to the prosecutor and tell him.

873
01:11:47,961 --> 01:11:50,120
He decided the question quickly.

874
01:11:50,120 --> 01:11:53,560
Everything together tomorrow, he whispered to himself.

875
01:11:53,561 --> 01:11:59,480
And strange to say, almost all his gladness and self-satisfaction passed in an instant.

876
01:11:59,481 --> 01:12:12,921
As he entered his room, he felt something like a touch of ice on his heart, like a recollection, or more exactly, a reminder of something agonizing and revolting that was in the room at that moment and had been there before.

877
01:12:13,240 --> 01:12:13,801
Who's that?

878
01:12:13,801 --> 01:12:16,200
Anybody read far enough to know?

879
01:12:16,521 --> 01:12:17,801
That's the devil.

880
01:12:17,801 --> 01:12:25,080
I mean, and why is it that he suddenly lost his resolution to confess?

881
01:12:25,080 --> 01:12:33,240
Because Dostoevsky has the idea that you can only do it impulsively, because otherwise all your bad character will take over.

882
01:12:33,240 --> 01:12:39,681
And he had this impulsive moment when he was going to go and confess right away to the police, and then he thought, wait till tomorrow.

883
01:12:40,000 --> 01:12:43,440
As soon as he thought, wait till tomorrow, he lost his momentum.

884
01:12:43,440 --> 01:12:45,200
He's not going to confess.

885
01:12:45,200 --> 01:12:52,881
In fact, he's going to go into a very bad direction next time because he gets to see the devil.
